	            $T(N) = 2T(N-1)+1\\$
	            $= 2T(N-2)+1+1\\$
	            $= 2T(N-3)+1+1+1\\$
	            $\cdot\\$
	            $\cdot\\$
	            $\cdot\\$
	            $=T(N-N) +$ . . . $+ 1+1+1\\$
	            With each recursuve call the size of $N$ is decreasing by $1$. At this rate it will continue decreasing until the base case of $T(1) =1$ is hit. It is multiplied by $2$ which is a constant and ignored leaving us with $O(N)$
	        \item[(b)]
