	            \underline{Expansion of recurrence relation:}\\
	            $T(N) = 4T(N/4)+N\\$
	            $= 4T(N/16)+N+N\\$
	            $= 4T(N/64)+N+N+N\\$
	            $\cdot\\$
	            $\cdot\\$
	            $\cdot\\$
	            $=T(N/N) +$ . . . $+N+N+N\\$
	            With each recursive call the size of $N$ is being divided by 4 which is a logarithmic pattern. It gets multiplied by $4$ which is a constant so it gets dropped leaving us with $O(log_{4}N)$ which is simplified to $O(logN)$
	        \item[(c)]
